Watch how the vague prompt flags safe code (TODO comments, accurate docstrings) as issues, while the specific criteria correctly identifies only the SQL injection in Snippet 1.


## Reference code

First, we'll create code samples that are a mix of real issues and false-positive-prone patterns.
The key: only 2 of 4 samples have real issues. A good prompt should flag those 2 and skip the rest.

